HEADWORD: Misdate
<hw>Mis*date"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Misdated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Misdating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put a false or
erroneous date on (a document).</def> <rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To assign an incorrect date to; <as>as, the fall of
Troy was <ex>misdated</ex> by medieval writers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>misdating</ent>⟦br⟧
